# Implementation

**Server-first:** `"use client"` only when needed.

**Suspense:** wrap only slices using `cookies()`, `headers()`, `connection()`, etc. Keep static / `'use cache'` shells **outside** Suspense. Prefer small parallel boundaries.

**Session (`auth-session.ts`):** `getSessionCached` (nullable; API → 401) · `requireAuthSession()` for dashboard pages/layouts/actions · `requireAuthSession(returnPath)` only outside dashboard gate (e.g. join). No `redirectTo` under `dashboard/layout`. Request-scoped `cache()` only — never `use cache` / revalidate session. Detail: [implementation.md](docs/agents/implementation.md#auth--session-srclibauth-sessionts).

**Copy:** English; `dashboard-nav-labels.ts` (orderly for later language changes — no i18n unless asked). **UI:** shadcn defaults, logical Tailwind — `ui-design.mdc`.

**Mutations:** `src/app/action/<feature>/` — validate → DB → cache (if needed) → return/redirect. See `caching` rule when editing actions.

```tsx
<Button render={<Link href="/dashboard" />}>Dashboard</Button>
```

